const bodyContent = `<div class="distance-bar">
  ⛽ Serving oilfield, pipeline, and energy crews working the Uintah Basin — call (435) 789-6625 for crew and corporate pricing
</div>

<div class="pbar">
  <div class="pi"><span class="ic">🚛</span><div><div class="label">Truck Parking</div><div class="sub">Work vehicles &amp; trailers welcome</div></div></div>
  <div class="pi"><span class="ic">🍳</span><div><div class="label">Early Breakfast</div><div class="sub">Hot breakfast before the drive out</div></div></div>
  <div class="pi"><span class="ic">📅</span><div><div class="label">Weekly &amp; Monthly</div><div class="sub">Discounted crew rates</div></div></div>
  <div class="pi"><span class="ic">🧺</span><div><div class="label">On-Site Laundry</div><div class="sub">Washers &amp; dryers on property</div></div></div>
  <div class="pi"><span class="ic">🏢</span><div><div class="label">Corporate Billing</div><div class="sub">Invoicing &amp; company accounts</div></div></div>
</div>

<div class="content-wrap">

  <div class="intro-pull rv">
    The Uintah Basin is one of the most productive energy regions in the western United States, and Vernal is its hub. Best Western Vernal Inn has been housing oilfield workers, pipeline crews, drilling teams, and energy contractors for years. We know what a field crew needs — and we've built our operation around delivering it reliably, week after week.
  </div>

  <section class="content-section rv">
    <h2>Why Crews Choose Best Western Vernal</h2>
    <p>There's a difference between a hotel that tolerates work crews and one that's genuinely set up for them. We're in the second category. Our team understands the rhythm of oilfield rotations — early starts, late arrivals, extended stays, and schedules that change without much notice.</p>
    <ul class="feat-list">
      <li>Weekly and monthly rates well below nightly pricing</li>
      <li>Truck, trailer, and equipment parking on property</li>
      <li>Hot breakfast available early — before the drive to the field</li>
      <li>On-site laundry for end-of-week gear cleanup</li>
      <li>Corporate billing and invoicing for company accounts</li>
      <li>Flexible check-in and check-out for rotating shifts</li>
      <li>In-room microwave and refrigerator in every room</li>
      <li>Free high-speed Wi-Fi — reliable enough for reporting and communication</li>
      <li>Pet-friendly rooms available for workers with dogs</li>
      <li>Best Western Rewards points on all stays</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section rv">
    <h2>Room Setup for the Long-Haul Worker</h2>
    <p>After a 12-hour day in the field, you want a real bed, a real shower, and a place that feels like something other than a truck cab. Our rooms are designed to function as a proper home base for extended stays — not just a place to sleep, but a place to decompress, eat, and get ready for tomorrow.</p>

    <div class="highlight-cards">
      <div class="hcard">
        <div class="hc-icon">🛏️</div>
        <strong>Quality Beds</strong>
        <span>Real mattresses, quality linens, and blackout curtains. Sleep matters when your days are hard.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hcard">
        <div class="hc-icon">🚿</div>
        <strong>Reliable Hot Water</strong>
        <span>Full bathroom with consistent hot water pressure. Not a truck stop. A real hotel room.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hcard">
        <div class="hc-icon">🍽️</div>
        <strong>In-Room Microwave &amp; Fridge</strong>
        <span>Store snacks, leftovers, and drinks. Prep simple meals on your own schedule.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hcard">
        <div class="hc-icon">📺</div>
        <strong>Flat-Screen TV</strong>
        <span>Decompress at the end of a long day. Cable included, no streaming device required.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hcard">
        <div class="hc-icon">💼</div>
        <strong>Desk &amp; Work Area</strong>
        <span>Complete field reports, handle paperwork, and stay in contact with the office.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hcard">
        <div class="hc-icon">📶</div>
        <strong>Fast Wi-Fi</strong>
        <span>Reliable enough for video calls, documentation uploads, and staying connected to your company.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section rv">
    <h2>Corporate &amp; Company Billing</h2>
    <p>We work directly with companies, drilling contractors, pipeline operators, and project managers to set up billing arrangements that make the administrative side easy. If you're booking for a crew, we can handle it as a single account.</p>
    <div class="tips-grid">
      <div class="tip-card">
        <span class="tip-icon">🏢</span>
        <p><strong>Company accounts.</strong> Establish a house account for ongoing crew bookings. One invoice per billing cycle rather than individual receipts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <span class="tip-icon">🧾</span>
        <p><strong>Itemized invoicing.</strong> Detailed receipts for expense reporting and per diem documentation. We understand the paperwork requirements.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <span class="tip-icon">📋</span>
        <p><strong>Flexible crew management.</strong> Rotating personnel on the same account. Workers can check in and out as the rotation schedule changes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <span class="tip-icon">📞</span>
        <p><strong>Direct line to management.</strong> Call <a href="tel:4357896625">(435) 789-6625</a> to speak with someone who can actually make decisions on pricing and logistics.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section rv">
    <h2>The Uintah Basin Energy Landscape</h2>
    <p>The Uintah Basin sits atop one of the most significant hydrocarbon-bearing formations in the Rocky Mountain region. Oil and gas production, pipeline infrastructure, and associated services have driven the local economy for decades. Vernal serves as the operational hub — where crews base out of, where supplies are sourced, and where the workforce lives between rotations.</p>
    <p>If your project is anywhere in the basin — from the Wasatch Front to the Colorado border, from the Wyoming line down to the Book Cliffs — Vernal is almost certainly your closest full-service city, and Best Western is your most complete lodging option in it.</p>
    <div class="attraction-cards">
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>📍 Central Vernal Location</strong>
        <p>Walking distance to fuel, restaurants, hardware, and supply runs. Everything a crew needs within a few miles.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>🚛 Truck-Friendly Property</strong>
        <p>Designed to accommodate work vehicles. No complaints from residential neighbors, no narrow parking lots.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>⛽ Near US-40 Corridor</strong>
        <p>Quick access to the main artery through the basin. Efficient drive to sites across the region.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>🏥 Near Vernal Services</strong>
        <p>Ashley Regional Medical Center and urgent care facilities nearby — important for crews on long rotations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section rv">
    <h2>Better Than a Man Camp</h2>
    <p>Temporary workforce housing camps are common in the basin, but they're not the only option — and for many workers, they're not the best one. A hotel with weekly rates offers everything a man camp does, plus things it doesn't.</p>
    <div class="included-box">
      <h3>What You Get at Best Western That a Man Camp Typically Doesn't Offer</h3>
      <div class="included-grid">
        <div class="inc-item">Hot breakfast included daily</div>
        <div class="inc-item">Private room — not a bunk</div>
        <div class="inc-item">Private bathroom</div>
        <div class="inc-item">In-room TV and Wi-Fi</div>
        <div class="inc-item">In-room fridge and microwave</div>
        <div class="inc-item">No shared sleeping quarters</div>
        <div class="inc-item">Best Western Rewards points</div>
        <div class="inc-item">Housekeeping service</div>
        <div class="inc-item">On-site laundry</div>
        <div class="inc-item">No camp curfews or restrictions</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="savings-tip">
      <p><strong>Bottom line:</strong> For workers on a per diem, a private hotel room at a weekly rate often comes close to the per diem ceiling — meaning the company covers most or all of it, and the worker gets a real room instead of a bunk. Call us to run the numbers for your situation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section rv">
    <h2>How to Book Housing for Your Crew</h2>
    <p>The simplest way is a phone call. Tell us how many people, how long the rotation, and whether you need corporate billing set up. We'll handle the rest.</p>
    <ul class="feat-list">
      <li>Call <a href="tel:4357896625">(435) 789-6625</a> — speak directly with the front desk</li>
      <li>Text the same number for quick confirmations</li>
      <li>Email available for formal corporate account setup</li>
      <li>Individual bookings also available at <a href="https://bestwesternvernalinn.com">bestwesternvernalinn.com</a></li>
      <li>Book early during busy basin periods — rooms fill fast</li>
      <li>Let us know about pets, parking needs, or special requirements upfront</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="pro-tip">
      <p><strong>For project managers:</strong> If you have a crew coming in for a multi-week project, reach out before the crew arrives. Setting up the account in advance makes check-in smooth for everyone, especially on day-shift starts at 4 or 5 a.m.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</div><!-- /content-wrap -->

